(31, 'Ultraprocessed Foods Linked To Ovarian And Other Cancer Deaths, Study Finds', 10, 15, '<div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\">Eating more ultraprocessed foods raises the risk of developing and dying from cancer, especially ovarian cancer, according to a new study of over 197,000 people in the United Kingdom, over half of whom were women.<p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\"></p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Overly processed foods include prepackaged soups, sauces, frozen pizza and ready-to-eat meals, as well as hot dogs, sausages, french fries, sodas, store-bought cookies, cakes, candies, doughnuts, ice cream and many more.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">“Ultra-processed foods are produced with industrially derived ingredients and often use food additives to adjust colour, flavour, consistency, texture, or extend shelf life,” said first author Dr. Kiara Chang, a National Institute for Health and Care Research fellow at Imperial College London’s School of Public Health, in a statement.</p></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">“Our bodies may not react the same way to these ultra-processed ingredients and additives as they do to fresh and nutritious minimally processed foods,” Chang said.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">However, people who eat more ultra-processed foods also tend to “drink more fizzy drinks and less tea and coffee, as well as less vegetables and other foods associated with a healthy dietary pattern,” said Duane Mellor, a registered dietitian and senior teaching fellow at Aston Medical School in Birmingham, UK, in an email.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">“This could mean that it may not be an effect specifically of the ultra-processed foods themselves, but instead reflect the impact of a lower intake of healthier food,” said Mellor, who was not involved in the study.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Risk increased with consumption</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">The study, published Tuesday in the journal eClinicalMedicine, looked at the association between eating ultraprocessed foods and 34 different types of cancer over a 10-year period.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Researchers examined information on the eating habits of 197,426 people who were part of the UK Biobank, a large biomedical database and research resource that followed residents from 2006 to 2010.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">The amount of ultraprocessed foods consumed by people in the study ranged from a low of 9.1% to a high of 41.4% of their diet, the study found.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Eating patterns were then compared with medical records that listed both diagnoses and deaths from cancer.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Each 10% increase in ultraprocessed food consumption was associated with a 2% increase in developing any cancer, and a 19% increased risk for being diagnosed with ovarian cancer, according to a statement issued by Imperial College London.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Deaths from cancers also increased, the study found. For each additional 10% increase in ultraprocessed food consumption, the risk of dying from any cancer increased by 6%, while the risk of dying from ovarian cancer rose by 30%, according to the statement.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-col