(32, 'Ultraprocessed Foods Linked To Ovarian And Other Cancer Deaths, Study Finds', 10, 15, '<div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\">Eating more ultraprocessed foods raises the risk of developing and dying from cancer, especially ovarian cancer, according to a new study of over 197,000 people in the United Kingdom, over half of whom were women.<p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\"></p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Overly processed foods include prepackaged soups, sauces, frozen pizza and ready-to-eat meals, as well as hot dogs, sausages, french fries, sodas, store-bought cookies, cakes, candies, doughnuts, ice cream and many more.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">“Ultra-processed foods are produced with industrially derived ingredients and often use food additives to adjust colour, flavour, consistency, texture, or extend shelf life,” said first author Dr. Kiara Chang, a National Institute for Health and Care Research fellow at Imperial College London’s School of Public Health, in a statement.</p></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">“Our bodies may not react the same way to these ultra-processed ingredients and additives as they do to fresh and nutritious minimally processed foods,” Chang said.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">However, people who eat more ultra-processed foods also tend to “drink more fizzy drinks and less tea and coffee, as well as less vegetables and other foods associated with a healthy dietary pattern,” said Duane Mellor, a registered dietitian and senior teaching fellow at Aston Medical School in Birmingham, UK, in an email.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">“This could mean that it may not be an effect specifically of the ultra-processed foods themselves, but instead reflect the impact of a lower intake of healthier food,” said Mellor, who was not involved in the study.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Risk increased with consumption</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">The study, published Tuesday in the journal eClinicalMedicine, looked at the association between eating ultraprocessed foods and 34 different types of cancer over a 10-year period.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Researchers examined information on the eating habits of 197,426 people who were part of the UK Biobank, a large biomedical database and research resource that followed residents from 2006 to 2010.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">The amount of ultraprocessed foods consumed by people in the study ranged from a low of 9.1% to a high of 41.4% of their diet, the study found.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Eating patterns were then compared with medical records that listed both diagnoses and deaths from cancer.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Each 10% increase in ultraprocessed food consumption was associated with a 2% increase in developing any cancer, and a 19% increased risk for being diagnosed with ovarian cancer, according to a statement issued by Imperial College London.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">Deaths from cancers also increased, the study found. For each additional 10% increase in ultraprocessed food consumption, the risk of dying from any cancer increased by 6%, while the risk of dying from ovarian cancer rose by 30%, according to the statement.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">“These associations persisted after adjustment for a range of socio-demographic, smoking status, physical activity, and key dietary factors,” the authors wrote.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">When it comes to death from cancer among women, ovarian cancer is ranked fifth, “accounting for more deaths than any other cancer of the female reproductive system,” noted the American Cancer Society.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">“The findings add to previous studies showing an association between a greater proportion of ultra-processed foods (UPFs) in the diet and a higher risk of obesity, heart attacks, stroke, and type 2 diabetes,” said Simon Steenson, a nutrition scientist at the British Nutrition Foundation, a charity partially supported by food producers and manufacturers. Steenson was not involved in the new study.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\">“However, an important limitation of these previous studies and the new analysis published today is that the findings are observational and so do not provide evidence of a clear causal link between UPFs and cancer, or the risk of other diseases,” Steenson said in an email.</p></div></div><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: jost; font-size: 18px;\"><div data-v-0c05764f=\"\" style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000;\"><p style=\"--tw-border-opacity:1; border-color: rgba(229,231,235,var(--tw-border-opacity)); --tw-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-inset:var(--tw-empty, ); --tw-ring-offset-width:0px; --tw-ring-offset-color:#fff; --tw-ring-color:rgba(59,130,246,0.5); --tw-ring-offset-shadow:0 0 #0000; --tw-ring-shadow:0 0 #0000; margin-bottom: 1.5em !important; line-height: 1.7 !important;\"><br></p></div></div>', '2023-04-05 06:53:23', NULL, 1, 'Ultraprocessed-Foods-Linked-To-Ovarian-And-Other-Cancer-Deaths,-Study-Finds', '31d4ce1f54429556d32cc5c606b9e2e2.png', NULL, 'admin', NULL);
